{"key":"processedPost-13163932","value":{"id":13163932,"first":13163004,"last":13164874,"when":1283953811,"utime":"09/08/10 04:50 PM","content":"Do NOT tape or otherwise cover the holes in a shotgun terrarium.&nbsp; You don't want to keep contaminants out.&nbsp; You want to let fresh air in, and lots of it.&nbsp; Fresh circulating air is the number one pinning trigger and also the number one contam prevention measure.&nbsp; You need sterile procedure when you're colonizing your jars.&nbsp; Once the cakes or other substrate is fully colonized, it will fend for itself, unless it's sitting in wet, stale air.<br /><br />Build a <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shotgun terrarium</a> per the tek, and pay attention to the section on <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek#lighting\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">lighting</a>.<br /><br />No more linking to the post office for misuse of supplies.&nbsp; That's been a rule around here for many years.&nbsp; Besides, it's bad advice and all it would do is screw up the operation of the terrarium.&nbsp; Air won't freely pass through tyvek, so it would prevent pinning and lead to contamination due to stale, still air.<br />RR","title":"Re: Shotgun terrarium/contam question.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}